{"expireTime":9007200839544229000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-html-94c53108dfd252a6f8bb77cd5de96e49-gatsby-plugin-sharpgatsby-remark-imagesgatsby-remark-responsive-iframegatsby-remark-prismjsgatsby-remark-copy-linked-filesgatsby-remark-smartypantsgatsby-remark-emojis-","val":"<p><strong>This blog would not have existed in the first place if it weren’t for the many creative individuals that continue to inspire me until today</strong>. And one of these people was no other than <strong>Steve Jobs</strong> – the visionary of Apple who died yesterday at the age of 56, (such a short time here on earth!) but whose legacy will live on for generations. He was a personal hero of my father (an advertising executive in the Philippines), who once told me that he wouldn’t mind working for Steve serving him coffee.</p>\n<p>I am a fan of Apple products – I literally wake up looking at my Ipod and use it watching videos before I sleep so it has become a huge part of my life. These gadgets have revolutionized our lives in the 21st century but more than that, I love the idea that Apple was headed by a <strong>cult figure like Steve Jobs</strong>. I honestly think that there is no giant corporation here on Earth headed by a leader as inspiring as Steve. It was what he stood for. <strong>He was a college dropout – an underdog with a relentless passion to create things that will change the world</strong>.</p>\n<p>\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n  \n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3fefa291d07a77b4fc0c08f902cda7fb/c08c5/rip_stevejobs_imanhd.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 640px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 73.00000000000001%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"rip stevejobs imanhd\"\n        title=\"On Apple’s website today\"\n        src=\"/static/3fefa291d07a77b4fc0c08f902cda7fb/c08c5/rip_stevejobs_imanhd.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3fefa291d07a77b4fc0c08f902cda7fb/e07e9/rip_stevejobs_imanhd.jpg 200w,\n/static/3fefa291d07a77b4fc0c08f902cda7fb/066f9/rip_stevejobs_imanhd.jpg 400w,\n/static/3fefa291d07a77b4fc0c08f902cda7fb/c08c5/rip_stevejobs_imanhd.jpg 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n  <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">On Apple’s website today</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n      </p>\n<p>But even if we have no desire to change the world, even if we only want to “contribute a verse”, in whatever job we have whether in art or in menial things, <strong>Steve encouraged us to seek our passion and never settle</strong>. I think artists and creative people have so much to learn from Steve’s philosophy.</p>\n<p>It wasn’t just a marketing strategy when he said “Think different”, as part of the slogan of his Apple commercials. Yeah, this man wanted to sell a lot of products and probably wanted to beat his best rival Bill Gates but his mission was other-wordly. <strong>He was encouraging us to find our creative voice and in way he wanted us to make our short sojourn here on earth worth the ride</strong>. So to you, Steve Jobs, thank you for inspiring us not to be mediocre. Thank you for being a big part of our creative spirit.</p>\n<p>\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n  \n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/057493739b7924f7d8ef06723838f30d/8473b/stevejobs_apple_atj4s2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 395px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 78.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"stevejobs apple atj4s2\"\n        title=\"Steve Jobs. Photo by Marco Paköeningrat\"\n        src=\"/static/057493739b7924f7d8ef06723838f30d/8473b/stevejobs_apple_atj4s2.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/057493739b7924f7d8ef06723838f30d/e07e9/stevejobs_apple_atj4s2.jpg 200w,\n/static/057493739b7924f7d8ef06723838f30d/8473b/stevejobs_apple_atj4s2.jpg 395w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 395px) 100vw, 395px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n  <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Steve Jobs. Photo by Marco Paköeningrat</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n      </p>\n<p><strong>Great Quotes from Steve Jobs:</strong></p>\n<p>“<strong>You have to trust in something — your gut, destiny, life, karma</strong>, whatever. This approach has never let me down, and it has made all the difference in my life.” (Steve Jobs, 2005)</p>\n<p>“Your time is limited, so don’t waste it living someone else’s life. Don’t be trapped by dogma — which is living with the results of other people’s thinking. <strong>Don’t let the noise of others’ opinions drown out your own inner voice</strong>. And most important, have the courage to follow your heart and intuition. They somehow already know what you truly want to become. Everything else is secondary.” (Steve Jobs, 2005)</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\" style=\"padding-bottom: 78.90625%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 2em\" > <iframe allowfullscreen class=\"youtube-player\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/UF8uR6Z6KLc?wmode=transparent&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;iv_load_policy=3&amp;showsearch=0&amp;rel=0&amp;theme=dark\" title=\"YouTube video player\" type=\"text/html\" style=\" position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; \"></iframe> </div>\n<figcaption>Commencement speech of Steve Jobs in Stanford in 2005</figcaption>\n<div class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 2em\" > <iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/cFEarBzelBs\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen style=\" position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; \"></iframe> </div>\n<figcaption>Think Different from Apple</figcaption>\n<p>Related Links:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.forbes.com/sites/techonomy/2011/10/06/steve-jobss-legacythink-different/\" title=\"Forbes: Steve Jobs\">Steve Jobs Legacy: Think Different from Adam Ludwig for Forbes  </a> <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/technology/2011/oct/06/steve-jobs-world-more-beautiful\" title=\"Jonathan Jones: Steve Jobs\">How Steve Jobs made the world beautiful from Jonathan Jones for the Guardian</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2011/10/06/national/main20116647.shtml\" title=\"CBS News: Steve Jobs\">Steve Jobs saw digital future, world followed CBSNews</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://news.cnet.com/8301-13579_3-20116821-37/steve-jobs-and-the-business-of-design/\" title=\"Steve Jobs on Cnet news\">Steve Jobs and the business of design by Jay Green for Cnet News</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.computerworld.com/s/article/9220610/Tech_elite_share_Jobs_tributes_on_Google_Facebook\" title=\"Computerworld: Steve Jobs\">How Steve Jobs Touched My Life: Readers Speak from Information Week Tech elite share Jobs’ Tributes on Google+ Facebook for Computerworld</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.wired.com/gadgetlab/2011/10/remembering-steve-jobs-web/\" title=\"Wired News: Steve Jobs\">Remembering Steve Jobs across the web from Wired News</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/industry/legal-and-management/q-a-u2-manager-paul-mcguinness-reflects-1005395422.story\" title=\"Paul Mcguinness on Steve Jobs\">Q&#x26;A: U2 Manager Paul McGuinness Reflects on Steve Jobs’ Passing</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.irishcentral.com/news/U2s-Bono-defends-Apples-Steve-Jobs-lack-of-philanthropy-129402108.html\" title=\"Bono and Steve Jobs\">U2’s Bono defend’s Apple’s Steve Jobs’ lack of philanthropy</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n  \n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/81e8a01a9dcebfc963560a82790d9051/863e1/imourn_zg2xp3.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 225px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 133.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"imourn zg2xp3\"\n        title=\"Photo by kgrz\"\n        src=\"/static/81e8a01a9dcebfc963560a82790d9051/863e1/imourn_zg2xp3.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/81e8a01a9dcebfc9